So I went down the rabbit hole, and am seriously getting Big Short v2: cryptocurrency redux vibes. They take custody of binance and coinbase deposits, and in turn, created their own network called "Silvergate Exchange Network" to fund loans, which is collateralized by bitcoin. This statement is worrying to me. I'm not saying it will happen, but I wouldn't be surprised if btc collapsed and suddenly they're stuck with worthless collateral on bad loans.

&#x200B;

I will agree that what they're doing in the financial technology space is unprecedented, but definitely not without risk. I'll be watching this one closely.

